The paper deals with text recognition in scene images and video frames, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed approach involves using hidden Markov models (HMM) for date spotting, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
